modules.description: Provides operations for inserting, searching, and traversing elements in a binary tree structure. Works with a custom tree type composed of nodes containing values and left-right child pointers. Used to efficiently manage hierarchical data in applications requiring fast lookup and ordered insertion.

Calculates the height, number of leaves, and internal nodes of a binary tree, and extracts internal node values. Determines if a tree is symmetric, strictly structured, or a left/right comb, and checks for perfect tree properties. Operates on a custom binary tree type where each node contains a value and references to left and right children.
